@NODE Set_Config "SET CONFIG OPTION"

    Short-cut: right Amiga + E

    This option open the @{"CONFIGURATION WINDOW" link Configuration_Window}
    and let you to set the configuration.
    The @{"CONFIGURATION WINDOW" link Configuration_Window} can also be opened
    choosing the option @{"CONFIG" link Config} of the menu @{"WINDOWS" link Windows}.

    @{"INDEX" link Main}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Save_Config "SAVE CONFIG OPTION"

    Short-cut: right Amiga + S

    This option let you to save the current configuration.
    The configuration can be modified choosing the option
    @{"SET CONFIG" link Set_Config} from the menu @{"PROJECT" link Project}
    or choosing the option @{"CONFIG" link Config} of the menu
    @{"WINDOWS" link Windows}.

    @{"INDEX" link Main}
@ENDNODE

@NODE About_BUM "ABOUT BUM OPTION"

    Short-cut: right Amiga + B

    This option show you information about the program and its author.

    @{"INDEX" link Main}
@ENDNODE

@NODE About_USER "ABOUT USER OPTION"

    Short-cut: right Amiga + U

    This option show information about the registrered user of BUM.

    @{"INDEX" link Main}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Iconify "ICONIFY OPTION"

    Short-cut: right Amiga + I

    This option inconify BUM, that is "freeze" the program windows, deallocate
    the most  number of resources as possible (screen, windows), place an icon
    called BUM on the WB screen and wait that the user click on that icon.
    When it happens the resources are reallocated and the program came back to the
    original state.

    @{"INDEX" link Main}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Quit "QUIT OPTION"

    Short-cut: right Amiga + Q

    This option give to the system all the resources allocated and quit
    from the program.

    @{"INDEX" link Main}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Config "CONFIG OPTION"

    Short-cut: right Amiga + C

    This option open the @{"CONFIGURATION WINDOW" link Configuration_Window}
    that allow you to modify the configuration.
    The @{"CONFIGURATION WINDOW" link Configuration_Window} can be opened
    also choosing the option @{"SET CONFIG" link Set_Config} of the menu
    @{"PROJECT" link Project}.
    The configuration can be saved choosing the option @{"SAVE CONFIG" link Save_Config}
    of the menu @{"PROJECT" link Project}.

    @{"INDEX" link Main}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Areas "AREAS OPTION"

    Short-cut: right Amiga + A

    This option open the @{"AREA WINDOW" link Area_Window} by the which
    you can edit the areas of the current BBS.

    @{"INDEX" link Main}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Print "PRINT OPTION"

    Short-cut: right Amiga + P

    This option open the @{"PRINT WINDOW" link Print_Window}: it let
    the user to print info about BBSs.

    @{"INDEX" link Main}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Search "SEARCH OPTION"

    Short-cut: right Amiga + R

    This option open the @{"SEARCH WINDOW" link Search_Window}: it let
    the user to search info on BBS lists.

    @{"INDEX" link Main}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Storia_BUM "HISTORY"

    Begin:          23-12-1994
    Release 1:      25-07-1995
    Release 1.01:   16-08-1995

    The code has been reordered.
    General optimization.
    Some bugs in short-cuts have been fixed.

    Release 1.3:    28-8-1995

    The read of archieves has been speed up.
    Added menu "WINDOWS" and the short-cuts.
    Iconify option.
    Insert sorted option.
    Area window.
    Print window.

    Release 1.5:    17-9-1995

    Optimization of some part of the code.
    Search window.

    Release 1.5.1:  24-9-1995

    The iconify option has been improved.
    The search window has been improved.

    Release 1.5.2:  26-9-1995

    Minor bug fix.

    Release 1.5.3:  27-9-1995

    Minor bug fix.

    @{"INDEX" link Main}
@ENDNODE
                       
